{
  "texts": [
    "In their later paper, Yeh et al. (2022) acknowledge the disadvantages of considering only the last layer writing, \"that choice critically affects the similarity component of data influence and leads to inferior results.\"",
    "Yeh et al. (2022) further state that the feature representations in the final layer-and by extension representer point's influence estimates-can be \"too reductive.\"",
    "In short, Yeh et al.'s (2018) representer point method is highly scalable and efficient but is only suitable to detect behaviors that are obvious in the model's final linear layer.",
    "Related Methods",
    "Given the accuracy limitations of relying on last-layer similarity, limited follow-on work has adapted representer-point methods."
  ]
}